         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">21/3/64. ¶ Dear Mr Bentham ¶  ¶ As I had no letter from you by last mail I need not write to you but on a few trifling subjects. From the enclosed note you will perceive, that the money for vol II is ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">64.03.21a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>To George Bentham<seg style="font-style: normal; "> </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, f. 143.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">21/3/64.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Mr Bentham</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As I had no letter from you by last mail I need not write to you but on a few trifling subjects. From the enclosed note you will perceive, that the money for vol II is sent already by last mail.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-style: italic; ">MS is marked with a marginal cross against this line</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">, </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-style: italic; ">and a cross at the top left of the sheet.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> I have just passed the first portion of fragm. XXVII through the press &amp; introduced into it <name key="Echinocarpus%20Australis">Echinocarpus Australis</name> as <name key="Sloanea%20Australis">Sloanea Australis</name>, to which genus in reality all Echinocarpi belong.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B64.05.01, p. 91.</p>
               </note> I herewith send you a flowering specimen.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Will you bear in mind that Prof Lange has published in the last seed Catalogue of Copenhagen a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Sutherlandia</hi>
               </seg> foliolata.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">‘from seed obtained from the Melbourne Garden ('Semina ex horto Melbournensi aceepimus'); see APNI.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> I have no doubt it is a <name key="Swainsona">Swainsona</name>. I have been engaged in placing the plants of various families into something like order. Amongst<seg style="font-weight: bold; "> </seg>
               <name key="Epacrideae">Epacrideae</name> I have several new species &amp; a remarkable new genus with connate anthers, to which I have given in the current number of the fragmenta the name <name key="Michiea">Michiea</name>.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B64.05.01, p<seg style="color: #000000; ">. 95.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With kindest regards</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller.</p>
